    <div class="container">
        <h2>Available Courses</h2>
        <ul class="courses-list">
            <li>
                <h3>1. Breast Self-Examination, Prevention, Self-Care</h3>
                <p>This course emphasizes the importance of regular screening programs, recognizing warning symptoms, and self-care practices.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <h3>2. Principles of Lymphatic Drainage and Self-Massage</h3>
                <p>Learn the techniques of lymphatic drainage and self-massage for better body circulation and well-being.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <h3>3. Menstrual Cycle and Hormones</h3>
                <p>Understand the difference between the menstrual cycle and bleeding during menstruation, the phases of ovulation, and how to adjust your nutrition to your cycle.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <h3>4. Breastfeeding and Breast Care</h3>
                <p>Proper techniques and essential care for breastfeeding mothers.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <h3>5. The Science of Sex</h3>
                <p>Discuss common sexual health concerns and provide practical solutions to problems and questions.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <h3>6. Support for IVF Preparation</h3>
                <p>Offering guidance and support for women preparing for assisted reproductive technologies such as IVF.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <h3>7. Wound Dressing and First Aid Course</h3>
                <p>Learn how to properly care for wounds, understand bandaging techniques, and handle first aid situations effectively.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <h3>8. Skin and Hair Care in Relation to Your Cycle</h3>
                <p>Understand how your menstrual cycle affects your skin and hair, and how to adjust your skincare routine accordingly.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <h3>9. Everything You Need to Know About Labor</h3>
                <p>Learn about childbirth, what to expect, and how to prepare both physically and mentally for the experience.</p>
            </li>
